  "prompt": "What are some visible signs of pregnancy?",
  "response": "Here are some common visible signs of pregnancy:\n\n1. Physical Changes\n- Missed menstrual period\n- Enlarged/swollen breasts\n- Darkening of nipples\n- Weight gain\n- Expanding belly/baby bump\n- Widening hips\n\n2. Skin Changes\n- Increased skin pigmentation\n- Stretch marks\n- Acne or skin glow\n- Visible veins\n\n3. Body Changes\n- Swollen feet and ankles\n- Increased breast size\n- Changes in body shape\n- Possible slight abdominal swelling\n\n4. Facial Changes\n- Fuller face\n- Changes in skin complexion\n- Potential hormonal acne\n\n5. Other Noticeable Signs\n- Visible fetal movement in later stages\n- Changes in posture\n- Potentially larger waistline\n\nRemember that pregnancy symptoms vary between individuals, and not all women experience the same signs. A pregnancy test and medical confirmation are the most reliable ways to determine pregnancy.",
